      "message": "https://docs.python.org/3/library/subprocess.html states \"If env is not None, it must be a mapping that defines the environment variables for the new process; these are used instead of the default behavior of inheriting the current process’ environment.\"\n\nI tested this behavior with a basic script instead of running the actual cronjob in a pod.\n\n```\nimport subprocess\n\nresult \u003d subprocess.run(\n    [\"env\"],\n    check\u003dTrue,\n    capture_output\u003dTrue,\n    text\u003dTrue\n)\n\nprint(result.stdout)\n```\nThis prints my computer\u0027s env variables.",
